      <aside class="calc-sidebar">
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h2>What is net salary?</h2>
          <p>Net salary (take-home pay) is the amount you actually receive in your bank account after all deductions — income tax (IRPF in Spain) and social security contributions. The difference between gross and net can be significant, typically between 20% and 35% of gross salary.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
          <details>
            <summary>What deductions are taken from gross salary?</summary>
            <p>In Spain, two main deductions apply — Social Security contributions (approximately 6.35% paid by the employee) and income tax withholding (IRPF), which ranges from 19% to 47% depending on your income bracket.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>How much net salary with €30,000 gross?</summary>
            <p>With €30,000 gross annually, the approximate monthly net salary is €1,850–€1,950, depending on your personal situation.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Is this calculator accurate?</summary>
            <p>It is an approximation based on Spanish 2024 tax rates. For an exact calculation use the official Spanish Tax Agency simulator.</p>
          </details>
